01:24:30.939 --> 01:24:32.442
You've seen them sales
on <i>Thriller.</i>

1452
01:24:32.461 --> 01:24:33.443
-Huh?
-Mm-hmm.

1453
01:24:33.508 --> 01:24:34.987
People are gonna be
climbing the walls.

1454
01:24:38.111 --> 01:24:39.948
Is Michael gonna be there?

1455
01:24:44.559 --> 01:24:45.789
Of course Michael's
gonna be there.

1456
01:24:45.920 --> 01:24:47.522
Hmm. That's good to hear.

1457
01:24:48.523 --> 01:24:50.424
Now. what's in it for me?

1458
01:24:53.360 --> 01:24:54.996
I've been watching you. Don.

1459
01:24:55.180 --> 01:24:57.684
-I watch you like a hawk.
-Hmm.

1460
01:24:57.703 --> 01:24:59.428
I love the way
you promote your fighters.

1461
01:24:59.567 --> 01:25:01.722
-Uh-huh.
-You're the king of marketing.

1462
01:25:01.936 --> 01:25:04.224
You know. I just. uh.
I think that you and I.

1463
01:25:04.237 --> 01:25:06.074
if we came together.
we could. uh...

1464
01:25:08.145 --> 01:25:09.510
We could form
a good partnership.

1465
01:25:09.551 --> 01:25:10.550
Me and you?

1466
01:25:10.569 --> 01:25:11.804
I'll cut you a good deal.

1467
01:25:13.313 --> 01:25:14.549
I like deals.

1468
01:25:21.388 --> 01:25:22.590
I need...

1469
01:25:23.256 --> 01:25:24.659
this for my boys.

1470
01:25:25.492 --> 01:25:26.828
I need it.

1471
01:25:27.080 --> 01:25:28.748
You know.
I think they deserve

1472
01:25:28.767 --> 01:25:31.042
the Rolls-Royce
of sponsorships.

1473
01:25:31.065 --> 01:25:34.379
I mean. merchandising.
marketing. you hear me?

1474
01:25:34.616 --> 01:25:36.250
I mean. it's got to be huge.

1475
01:25:36.380 --> 01:25:37.812
And only you and I
could do it.

1476
01:25:39.747 --> 01:25:40.982
It'll be called...

1477
01:25:41.836 --> 01:25:44.138
-"The Victory Tour."
-Hmm.

1478
01:25:48.644 --> 01:25:51.021
I may have something for you.

1479
01:25:51.343 --> 01:25:54.055
Pepsi. They want to
get back in the game.

1480
01:25:54.122 --> 01:25:55.957
Michael could be
the face of the brand.

1481
01:25:56.024 --> 01:25:57.959
do some commercials.

1482
01:25:58.026 --> 01:25:59.446
All right.

1483
01:26:00.193 --> 01:26:01.696
-I can see it.
-Yeah.

1484
01:26:03.745 --> 01:26:05.064
But you wouldn't be
bullshitting me.

1485
01:26:05.083 --> 01:26:06.519
would you. Joe?

1486
01:26:08.341 --> 01:26:10.778
Because if you
can't get Michael...

1487
01:26:21.885 --> 01:26:24.317
I love it! Now. that's
my favorite part.

1488
01:26:30.931 --> 01:26:32.599
I'm gonna
leave it to you. Michael.

1489
01:26:32.805 --> 01:26:33.833
You can't go yet.

1490
01:26:33.851 --> 01:26:35.536
No. I'm going to bed.
I'm tired.

1491
01:26:35.820 --> 01:26:37.554
You got to stay for the
ending. That's the best part.

1492
01:26:37.573 --> 01:26:39.861
Your mother is tired. baby.

1493
01:26:40.500 --> 01:26:43.137
Do me a favor. Make sure
you turn the lights off?

1494
01:26:43.615 --> 01:26:45.073
-Night. mother.
-Good night.

1495
01:27:21.481 --> 01:27:22.717
Why are you here?

1496
01:27:23.804 --> 01:27:25.806
What? Can't a father
visit his son?

1497
01:27:28.321 --> 01:27:31.358
Biggest-selling record
of all time

1498
01:27:31.384 --> 01:27:33.386
from a poor kid from Gary.

1499
01:27:34.282 --> 01:27:35.469
Who would have thought?

1500
01:27:36.168 --> 01:27:38.458
Me. I thought.

1501
01:27:44.484 --> 01:27:45.585
Come here.

1502
01:27:46.801 --> 01:27:48.603
Joseph. I know
you want something.

1503
01:27:53.748 --> 01:27:54.949
Michael...

1504
01:27:56.884 --> 01:27:59.086
I'm gonna need you
to tour with your brothers.

1505
01:28:00.581 --> 01:28:03.083
Now. I let you do
that album by yourself.

1506
01:28:04.297 --> 01:28:06.032
I'm gonna need you
to do this for me.

1507
01:28:07.903 --> 01:28:08.983
For your family.

1508
01:28:10.591 --> 01:28:12.760
I'm not a child
anymore. Joseph.

1509
01:28:13.828 --> 01:28:15.582
-And you're not my manager.
-Here we go.

1510
01:28:15.601 --> 01:28:17.736
I have to start
living my own life.

1511
01:28:19.786 --> 01:28:20.987
On my own.

1512
01:28:22.172 --> 01:28:23.671
Just like everyone else.

1513
01:28:23.738 --> 01:28:25.472
You ain't like everyone else.

1514
01:28:28.321 --> 01:28:29.345
So. you're trying to tell me

1515
01:28:29.364 --> 01:28:31.065
you want to be treated
like an adult?

1516
01:28:32.526 --> 01:28:33.847
All right.

1517
01:28:34.106 --> 01:28:37.658
You want to
see what the world is like

1518
01:28:38.897 --> 01:28:40.822
without a family
that protects you.

1519
01:28:43.248 --> 01:28:44.839
Without a family that...

1520
01:28:45.708 --> 01:28:47.447
understands you.

1521
01:28:47.948 --> 01:28:51.221
Nobody else will understand
you outside this place.

1522
01:28:51.451 --> 01:28:54.120
There you'll be with
all the money in the world.

1523
01:28:54.314 --> 01:28:56.216
surrounded by people
who'll say "yes"

1524
01:28:57.104 --> 01:28:59.084
to everything.

1525
01:29:00.867 --> 01:29:02.068
Is that what you want?

1526
01:29:06.800 --> 01:29:08.134
What kind of sense that make?

1527
01:29:16.390 --> 01:29:17.590
I'm gonna...

1528
01:29:18.270 --> 01:29:20.063
call Don King

1529
01:29:20.272 --> 01:29:22.029
and tell him
you're doing a tour.

1530
01:29:24.844 --> 01:29:26.813
I know you don't want
to let your family down.

1531
01:29:58.447 --> 01:30:00.478
<i>♪ You're a whole
new generation ♪</i>

1532
01:30:00.694 --> 01:30:02.439
<i>♪ You're lovin' what you do ♪</i>

1533
01:30:02.522 --> 01:30:04.524
<i>♪ Put a Pepsi in the motion ♪</i>

1534
01:30:04.571 --> 01:30:06.859
<i>♪ That choice is up to you
Hey-ey ♪</i>

1535
01:30:06.893 --> 01:30:08.828
Cut! Cut! Cut! Cut!

1536
01:30:09.123 --> 01:30:10.780
I'm cutting. guys!

1537
01:30:11.799 --> 01:30:14.134
All right. here's what I need.
I'm thinking...

1538
01:30:15.783 --> 01:30:18.451
I'm gonna move the camera in
while you're up here.

1539
01:30:18.783 --> 01:30:20.983
I need to get a close up
of you at the top.

1540
01:30:21.187 --> 01:30:23.390
so just feel the camera
as you come down.

1541
01:30:23.691 --> 01:30:25.359
-Okay.
-Okay. great. All right.

1542
01:30:25.545 --> 01:30:27.380
Okay. everybody.

1543
01:30:27.542 --> 01:30:28.674
Here we go.

1544
01:30:28.933 --> 01:30:31.218
What is this?
What do we got? Take six?

1545
01:30:31.565 --> 01:30:33.015
Lucky six. Lucky six.

1546
01:30:33.034 --> 01:30:34.911
Here we go. Energy. everybody!

1547
01:30:34.930 --> 01:30:37.266
You love the Jacksons.
You love the Jacksons.

1548
01:30:37.305 --> 01:30:39.140
You love Pepsi. Let's go!

1549
01:30:40.046 --> 01:30:41.648
A marker!

1550
01:30:42.216 --> 01:30:43.563
B mark!

1551
01:30:44.282 --> 01:30:45.245
C mark.

1552
01:30:45.265 --> 01:30:46.900
And playback.

1553
01:31:20.700 --> 01:31:21.801
Michael!

1554
01:31:23.436 --> 01:31:24.604
What happened?

1555
01:31:25.238 --> 01:31:26.941
-Mike. are you okay?
-Back up! Back up! Back up!

1556
01:31:26.960 --> 01:31:28.182
Bill. get him out of here!

1557
01:31:28.200 --> 01:31:29.720
I'm here! I'm here! I'm here. Michael!

1558
01:31:31.393 --> 01:31:33.419
Hey. you're gonna be okay.
okay? You're gonna be okay.

1559
01:31:33.446 --> 01:31:34.915
Come on. Mike.
Clear a path!

1560
01:31:38.420 --> 01:31:41.288
Out of my way!
Michael. I'm coming!

1561
01:31:41.746 --> 01:31:43.771
Get back! Get out of my way!
Clear a path!

1562
01:31:43.838 --> 01:31:45.973
Get back! Get back!

1563
01:31:47.141 --> 01:31:49.977
Clear a path!
Move! Move. please!

1564
01:31:50.044 --> 01:31:51.379
Michael!

1565
01:31:52.882 --> 01:31:54.050
Excuse me!

1566
01:32:24.831 --> 01:32:26.249
Hey. Kate. come on.

1567
01:32:28.517 --> 01:32:30.568
-Hey. I need to talk to you.
-Sir.

1568
01:32:30.587 --> 01:32:32.153
I'm his father.
Joseph Jackson.

1569
01:32:32.547 --> 01:32:33.754
This is his mother. Katherine.

1570
01:32:33.868 --> 01:32:35.718
-Hi. It's good to meet you.
-Very nice to meet you.

1571
01:32:35.737 --> 01:32:36.885
Thank you.

1572
01:32:37.024 --> 01:32:39.493
Well. your son is
in stable condition.

1573
01:32:39.608 --> 01:32:41.009
-All right.
-All right?

1574
01:32:41.076 --> 01:32:43.539
And. uh. we're trying to bring
his heart rate down.

1575
01:32:43.558 --> 01:32:44.765
but he's in a lot of pain.

1576
01:32:46.032 --> 01:32:47.467
Okay. When will he recover?

1577
01:32:47.860 --> 01:32:49.564
It's too soon to tell.

1578
01:32:49.807 --> 01:32:51.820
It's gonna be
a long road. all right?

1579
01:32:51.839 --> 01:32:54.842
He has third-degree burns
and substantial nerve damage.

1580
01:32:57.322 --> 01:32:58.679
Okay.

1581
01:32:58.823 --> 01:33:01.849
Do you think he'll ever be
able to perform again?

1582
01:33:02.124 --> 01:33:03.286
Ever?

1583
01:33:03.627 --> 01:33:04.751
Joseph.

1584
01:33:08.333 --> 01:33:11.545
Mr. Jackson.
your son almost died.

1585
01:33:11.608 --> 01:33:12.670
I know that.

1586
01:33:12.689 --> 01:33:14.883
Well. if that fire
had caught his clothes.

1587
01:33:14.967 --> 01:33:17.717
or burned over to his face
and eyes. he wouldn't be here.

1588
01:33:17.736 --> 01:33:19.594
I know my boy.

1589
01:33:20.011 --> 01:33:21.869
And the only thing
that's gonna heal him

1590
01:33:22.138 --> 01:33:23.771
is by getting
back on that stage.

1591
01:33:25.141 --> 01:33:26.508
That's where he lives.

1592
01:33:26.815 --> 01:33:28.180
I understand that. sir.

1593
01:33:28.228 --> 01:33:29.562
-Do you?
-But it's gonna be a while.

1594
01:33:29.581 --> 01:33:32.357
-All right.
-Yes. I do. But. Mr. Jackson...

1595
01:33:32.581 --> 01:33:34.984
he's gonna need
your support to get there.

1596
01:33:35.527 --> 01:33:36.585
I'm sorry.

1597
01:33:43.203 --> 01:33:45.578
It's unlikely
that'll grow back.

1598
01:33:46.038 --> 01:33:49.130
You'll need surgery
to laser the scar tissue

1599
01:33:49.196 --> 01:33:52.544
and stretch part of the scalp
over the burn.

1600
01:33:52.961 --> 01:33:56.006
All right? We'll insert an
implant to protect the scalp.

1601
01:33:56.285 --> 01:33:58.007
Will I have to wear a wig?

1602
01:33:58.139 --> 01:33:59.759
Well. right there on top.

1603
01:34:02.125 --> 01:34:04.347
What kind of wig?
Like. a full wig?

1604
01:34:04.604 --> 01:34:05.779
Hard to say.

1605
01:34:05.890 --> 01:34:08.209
There are prosthetic
hair weaves we can try.

1606
01:34:08.228 --> 01:34:09.664
but we won't know until we see

1607
01:34:09.683 --> 01:34:12.063
how the surgery goes
next week.

1608
01:34:19.594 --> 01:34:21.447
You'll. um...

1609
01:34:21.795 --> 01:34:23.931
You'll have to stay
on the Demerol for a while.

1610
01:34:24.240 --> 01:34:26.244
I don't want
to take medication.

1611
01:34:26.467 --> 01:34:27.997
I have to be honest.
Mr. Jackson.

1612
01:34:28.016 --> 01:34:29.414
you're gonna need them.

1613
01:34:30.171 --> 01:34:32.458
We have to replace
the implant periodically.

1614
01:34:32.507 --> 01:34:34.502
The nerves are
exposed up there.

1615
01:34:34.643 --> 01:34:36.343
You'll be in a lot of pain.

1616
01:34:39.246 --> 01:34:41.933
I'll let you rest.
but I'll be back later.

1617
01:34:50.476 --> 01:34:51.686
You see the number of people

1618
01:34:51.705 --> 01:34:53.941
who have already gathered
outside the hospital.

1619
01:34:54.499 --> 01:34:55.754
If that isn't a testament

1620
01:34:55.773 --> 01:34:58.318
to the star power of Michael
Jackson. I don't know what is.

1621
01:34:58.337 --> 01:34:59.515
The fans say
they won't go back

1622
01:34:59.534 --> 01:35:01.468
until Jackson's
all right.

1623
01:35:03.577 --> 01:35:04.907
All right.

1624
01:35:05.139 --> 01:35:06.784
All right. Joker.

1625
01:35:07.174 --> 01:35:08.610
Got all your favorites.

1626
01:35:08.745 --> 01:35:10.792
Golden Temple.
they send their love.

1627
01:35:10.811 --> 01:35:12.980
-Golden Temple's your favorite. Michael.
-Got some Mexican. Chinese.

1628
01:35:12.999 --> 01:35:14.075
Some fried chicken.

1629
01:35:14.094 --> 01:35:15.962
Even got these
little red candies you like.

1630
01:35:17.545 --> 01:35:20.892
Thanks. Bill.
You can just leave it there.

1631
01:35:21.120 --> 01:35:22.355
I'm not hungry.

1632
01:35:23.190 --> 01:35:24.693
Oh. Okay.

1633
01:35:28.443 --> 01:35:29.878
I'll leave you all to it.

1634
01:35:29.957 --> 01:35:32.594
-Okay. Thank you. Bill.
-Mm-hmm.

1635
01:36:00.488 --> 01:36:01.922
I'm sorry. Michael.

1636
01:36:06.233 --> 01:36:08.035
I should have protected you.

1637
01:36:09.719 --> 01:36:13.178
Mother. I don't want to
discuss this right now.

1638
01:36:14.454 --> 01:36:15.522
Okay.

1639
01:36:22.249 --> 01:36:23.861
No one could stop Joseph.

1640
01:36:27.461 --> 01:36:28.529
Nobody.

1641
01:36:37.257 --> 01:36:39.794
You just know that.
no matter what happens.

1642
01:36:40.654 --> 01:36:42.589
I'm gonna be here for you...

1643
01:36:43.704 --> 01:36:45.205
always.

1644
01:36:48.376 --> 01:36:50.013
I should get
some rest now. Mother.

1645
01:37:14.287 --> 01:37:15.922
It's not your fault.

1646
01:37:38.492 --> 01:37:40.861
We all need you. Michael!

1647
01:38:16.630 --> 01:38:17.997
How are you feeling?

1648
01:38:18.726 --> 01:38:19.834
I'm okay.

1649
01:38:20.061 --> 01:38:22.605
You know.
I'm still in a lot of pain.

1650
01:38:23.826 --> 01:38:26.066
But the doctors say
I'm healing. So...

1651
01:38:26.300 --> 01:38:27.480
Well. that's good news.

1652
01:38:28.387 --> 01:38:29.870
All these kids here...

1653
01:38:31.323 --> 01:38:32.514
They won't fully heal

1654
01:38:32.533 --> 01:38:34.990
and there's burns
all over their bodies.

1655
01:38:35.749 --> 01:38:37.203
It just breaks my heart.

1656
01:38:38.162 --> 01:38:39.455
It truly does.

1657
01:38:42.022 --> 01:38:43.525
You know.
it got me thinking...

1658
01:38:45.461 --> 01:38:47.171
I need to do more for them.

1659
01:38:48.256 --> 01:38:50.467
How much are we getting
for the accident?

1660
01:38:50.472 --> 01:38:52.718
It should be
around seven figures.

1661
01:38:53.080 --> 01:38:55.917
I need every penny donated
to the burn center here.

1662
01:38:57.104 --> 01:38:59.058
Please. you got to
make that happen.

1663
01:38:59.399 --> 01:39:00.533
Yeah. of course.

1664
01:39:03.733 --> 01:39:05.380
I'm getting really sleepy.

1665
01:39:07.519 --> 01:39:08.818
These pain meds.

1666
01:39:12.394 --> 01:39:13.429
You get some rest

1667
01:39:13.448 --> 01:39:15.283
and I'll come
check on you tomorrow.

1668
01:39:16.689 --> 01:39:17.690
Okay.

1669
01:39:20.204 --> 01:39:21.247
Did you bring that?

1670
01:39:21.266 --> 01:39:24.041
Oh. the mouse. yeah.
That's from me.

1671
01:39:25.559 --> 01:39:27.211
-I love that.
-Good.

1672
01:39:28.463 --> 01:39:30.750
-Thank you. Branca. See you.
-I'll see you tomorrow.

1673
01:39:32.574 --> 01:39:34.742
<i>If that boy
doesn't go on tour.</i>

1674
01:39:35.690 --> 01:39:37.805
everything we have
falls apart.

1675
01:39:38.139 --> 01:39:42.060
I'm talking deals.
sponsorships. our reputation.

1676
01:39:42.226 --> 01:39:43.833
Everything.
Everything just gone.

1677
01:39:43.852 --> 01:39:45.146
Everything here.

1678
01:39:46.654 --> 01:39:48.858
The boys won't be able
to tour anymore.

1679
01:39:49.400 --> 01:39:50.860
Not without Michael.

1680
01:39:51.158 --> 01:39:53.613
Your son
just got out of ICU.

1681
01:39:56.778 --> 01:39:58.043
Michael never wanted to do

1682
01:39:58.062 --> 01:39:59.463
The Victory Tour
to begin with.

1683
01:39:59.482 --> 01:40:02.117
You planned this entire thing
behind his back.

1684
01:40:13.948 --> 01:40:16.885
When are you gonna realize
he's on his own path?

1685
01:40:19.721 --> 01:40:22.155
And sometimes. you need
to get out of the way.

1686
01:40:25.946 --> 01:40:27.848
Otherwise.
you're gonna lose him.

1687
01:40:31.032 --> 01:40:32.667
What about the other boys?

1688
01:40:33.701 --> 01:40:35.537
They'll find their own path.

1689
01:40:51.701 --> 01:40:53.134
<i>You know something. Bill?</i>

1690
01:40:53.643 --> 01:40:54.654
What's that?

1691
01:40:54.674 --> 01:40:56.290
God's been very good to me.

1692
01:40:56.425 --> 01:40:58.082
That he has.

1693
01:40:59.299 --> 01:41:01.222
Not just the accident.

1694
01:41:01.596 --> 01:41:03.939
You know. I...
I almost died...

1695
01:41:05.679 --> 01:41:07.446
but I was given
a second chance.

1696
01:41:08.368 --> 01:41:09.571
Yeah. well...

1697
01:41:10.691 --> 01:41:12.191
God gave you a gift. son.

1698
01:41:13.541 --> 01:41:14.943
A platform...

1699
01:41:16.044 --> 01:41:17.822
to reach the whole world.

1700
01:41:19.581 --> 01:41:21.015
I can't ignore that.

1701
01:41:23.618 --> 01:41:24.719
No.

1702
01:41:27.748 --> 01:41:29.557
I have to shine my light.

1703
01:41:30.457 --> 01:41:32.795
